## 🟡 Table: `gold.dim_customers`

This dimension table stores customer details enriched with demographic and geographic data. It supports analytical queries by providing descriptive attributes for each customer.

### 📐 Schema

| Column Name      | Data Type       | Description                                                                 |
|------------------|------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `customer_key`   | `INT`            | Surrogate key uniquely identifying each customer record.                    |
| `customer_id`    | `INT`            | Unique numerical identifier assigned to each customer.                      |
| `customer_number`| `NVARCHAR(50)`   | Alphanumeric identifier used for tracking and referencing.                 |
| `first_name`     | `NVARCHAR(50)`   | Customer's first name.                                                     |
| `last_name`      | `NVARCHAR(50)`   | Customer's last name or family name.                                       |
| `country`        | `NVARCHAR(50)`   | Country of residence (e.g., 'Australia').                                  |
| `marital_status` | `NVARCHAR(50)`   | Marital status (e.g., 'Married', 'Single').                                |
| `gender`         | `NVARCHAR(50)`   | Gender (e.g., 'Male', 'Female', 'n/a').                                    |
| `birthdate`      | `DATE`           | Date of birth in YYYY-MM-DD format (e.g., 1971-10-06).                      |
| `create_date`    | `DATE`           | Date and time when the record was created.                                 |

> ✅ This table is part of the Gold Layer, optimized for business-level reporting and analysis.
